TableBuilder
============

Builder for creating tables inspired by ActionView::Helpers::FormHelper::FormBuilder.

Examples
=======

@front_men = [FrontMan.new(1, 'David St. Hubbins'), FrontMan.new(2, 'David Lee Roth')]

<% table_for(@front_men) do |t| %>
  <%= t.head('Id', 'Name') %>
  <% t.body_r do |front_man| %>
    <%= t.d(h(front_man.id)) %>
    <%= t.d(h(front_man.name)) %>
  <% end %>
<% end %>

You can also pass blocks to the d method

<%= t.d(:class => 'name') do %>
  <%= link_to(h(front_man.name), front_man_url) %>
<% end %>

All tags can have extra html options.

@drummers = [Drummer.new(1, 'John "Stumpy" Pepys'), Drummer.new(2, 'Eric "Stumpy Joe" Childs')]

<% table_for(@drummers, :html => { :id => 'spinal_tap', :class => 'drummers'}) do |t| %>
  <% t.body_r do |e| %>
    <%= t.d(h(e.id), :class => 'class') %>
    <%= t.d(h(e.name)) %>
  <% end %>
<% end %> 

... which produces the following html:

<table class="drummers" id="spinal_tap">
  <tbody><tr>
    <td class="class">1</td>
    <td>John &quot;Stumpy&quot; Pepys</td>
  </tr><tr>
    <td class="class">2</td>
    <td>Eric &quot;Stumpy Joe&quot; Childs</td>
  </tr></tbody>
</table>


Calendar Table
================

calendar_for(objects, options)
All objects get sorted per day of the month

day(options)
day yields the day and the objects that for that day.
Which day that is, is decided by the calling the :day_method on the objects.

Calendar Example
================

@tasks = Task.this_month

<% calendar_for(@tasks) do |t| %>
  <%= t.head('mon', 'tue', 'wed', 'thu', 'fri', 'sat', 'sun') %>
  <% t.day(:day_method => :calendar_date) do |day, tasks| %>
    <small><%= day.day %></small><br />
    <% tasks.each do |task| %>
      <% if task.completed %>
        <small><%= h(task.name) %></small>
      <% else %>
        <h2><%= h(task.name) %></h2>
      <% end %>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
<% end %>


Install
=======

script/plugin install git://github.com/p8/table_builder.git


